annotationA: Transmembrane GTPase fzo; Essential transmembrane GTPase, which mediates mitochondrial fusion during spermatogenesis. In early spermatocytes, fusion of mitochondria give rise to two organelles named Nebenkern and constitutes an important step in mitochondria morphology, which is balanced between fusion and fission. Essential for fertility
annotationB: PTEN-induced putative kinase 1, isoform A; Protein kinase activity; ATP binding; protein binding; protein serine/threonine kinase activity
